Defending champions Malaysia powered into the  Thomas Cup final by taking a winning 3-0 lead over China in Tuesday's  semi-finals while Indonesia scored an upset win over South Korea to reach the  women's Uber Cup final.
Malaysia play either Indonesia or South Korea in Saturday's final. The  second semi-final is to be played on Wednesday.
Indonesia's surprising 4-1 win over the favourites South Korea secured a  berth in the women's final on Friday against China or Sweden.
